      • isExcluded

        public abstract boolean isExcluded(VirtualFile file)
        Returns true if file located under this directory is excluded from the project. If file is a directory it means that all of its content is recursively excluded from the project (except the sub-directories which are explicitly included back, e.g. module roots)
        Parameters:
        file - a file under the directory described by this instance.

      • isInLibrarySource

        public abstract boolean isInLibrarySource(VirtualFile file)
        Parameters:
        file - a file under the directory described by this instance.
        Returns:
        true if file located under this directory is located in library sources. If file is a directory it means that all of its content is recursively in not part of the libraries.
